                     <title xml:lang="en">Latin deed with Hebrew acknowledgment</title>
							
                     
                     
                     
                     <note>
								
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>Acknowledgment of receipt, written on the back of a Latin
charter) by Solomon of Paris to Richard de Malebys of £4.
                                    </p>
								
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>The Latin charter is the acquittance by Solomon of Paris
to Richard de Malebis for f£4 due to his lord Aaron, paid on
          Monday after Martinmas following the death of Geoffrey
[Kirtling], High-Dean of Lincoln, in part payment of "the great
  debt which he owes to my Lord Aaron, whereof I have appointed
 him a day [for settlement]. </p>
							
                     
                     
                     
                     </note>
							
                     
                     
                     
                     <quote xml:lang="he">"קבלתי ארבעה ליטר מריקארט חייה רעה ב' וישב קמג
                                מחובו הגדול שלמה מפריש ו[ח]תיכה עשיתי."</quote>
						
                  
                  
                  
                  </msItem>
					
               
               
               
               </msContents>
					
               
               
               
